<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="410" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1911,2008]" lastBlockId="9.[151,1437,151,357]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="410" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,718,1911,1936]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">
Description. Male 
<typeStatus box="[421,523,1911,1936]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<collectionCode box="[538,624,1911,1936]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/90vz-swjg" name="Museu Paraense Emilio Goeldi" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">MPEG</collectionCode>
29052).
</emphasis>
Total length: 2.43. Carapace with a longitudinal stripe of white scales on carapace and tufts of brown scales laterally (
<figureCitation box="[802,873,1947,1972]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,2008,2030]" captionTargetBox="[195,1396,1209,2001]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[193,1398,1209,2001]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Amphidraus caxiuanan sp. nov. A male Holotype, dorsal view; B same, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855445/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
